---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LinkButton from '../components/LinkButton.vue';
---

<BaseLayout title="Rewards4 — Case Study" description="Modernising the Rewards4 Platform — Migrating a multi-brand rewards ecosystem to a scalable, high-performance architecture.">
  <section class="case-study-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Case Study</p>
      <h1>Rewards4 Platform</h1>
      <p class="intro">Modernising a multi-brand rewards ecosystem to a scalable, high-performance architecture.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="case-study-content">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="case-study-panel">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>The Rewards4 platform powers a group of sports-focused loyalty websites, including:</p>
        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Rewards4Racing</li>
          <li>Rewards4Golf</li>
          <li>Rewards4RugbyLeague</li>
          <li>Rewards4Sport</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These platforms allow users to earn points through online shopping and redeem them with their favourite sports brands.</p>
        <p>I led the front-end modernisation of these sites, migrating them from a legacy architecture to a scalable, component-based system using Vue 3 and TypeScript—while also improving usability across the platform through incremental UX enhancements.</p>
      </article>

    <section class="case-study-content">
  <div class="container">


    <details class="case-study-panel">
      <summary>The Challenge</summary>

      <div class="case-study-panel-content">
        <p>The existing platform was built on a legacy stack that had become difficult to scale and maintain:</p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>C#, .NET Core Razor Pages</li>
          <li>SCSS and Bootstrap</li>
          <li>Heavy reliance on jQuery and CMS-driven rendering</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Key Issues</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Performance limitations caused by server-heavy rendering and inefficient front-end behaviour</li>
          <li>Inconsistent user experiences across multiple brand sites</li>
          <li>Duplicated effort when updating styles and features</li>
          <li>Slow development workflows due to limited component reuse</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>The Goal</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Modernise the front-end architecture</li>
          <li>Improve scalability and performance</li>
          <li>Standardise UX across brands</li>
          <li>Enable faster development workflows</li>
          <li>Improve usability without redesigning the core brand identity</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="case-study-panel">
      <summary>My Role</summary>

      <div class="case-study-panel-content">
        <p>I worked across both UX and front-end development, focusing on:</p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Leading the migration to Vue 3 and TypeScript</li>
          <li>Refactoring legacy jQuery-based patterns</li>
          <li>Designing a scalable multi-brand architecture</li>
          <li>Improving mobile usability and UI consistency</li>
          <li>Collaborating with backend developers on API integration</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="case-study-panel">
      <summary>Approach</summary>

      <div class="case-study-panel-content">
        <p><strong>Incremental Migration Strategy</strong></p>

        <p>
          Rather than rebuilding the platform all at once, I introduced a phased migration strategy focused on stability and continuous improvement.
        </p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Identified high-impact areas for refactoring</li>
          <li>Rebuilt features using Vue components</li>
          <li>Gradually replaced legacy functionality</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Component-Based Architecture</strong></p>

        <p>
          I introduced reusable UI components to replace duplicated logic across sites, enabling:
        </p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Consistent UI patterns</li>
          <li>Faster development</li>
          <li>Easier maintenance</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Tenant-Based Multi-Brand System</strong></p>

        <p>
          I helped implement a tenant-based structure where all brands shared a common platform while supporting brand-specific styling and configuration.
        </p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Shared platform architecture</li>
          <li>Configurable branding per site</li>
          <li>Reduced duplication across projects</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Performance Optimisation</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Reduced reliance on CMS-rendered content</li>
          <li>Shifted to API-driven data loading</li>
          <li>Loaded only required content per page</li>
          <li>Used Cloudflare for caching and delivery optimisation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="case-study-panel">
      <summary>Before vs After</summary>

      <div class="case-study-panel-content">
        <p><strong>Before</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>jQuery-driven interactions</li>
          <li>Server-rendered pages</li>
          <li>Duplicated styles across brands</li>
          <li>Slower development cycles</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>After</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Vue 3 component architecture</li>
          <li>API-driven front-end</li>
          <li>Shared system with configurable branding</li>
          <li>Faster and more scalable development workflows</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="case-study-panel">
      <summary>UX Improvements Within Constraints</summary>

      <div class="case-study-panel-content">
        <p>
          Due to brand consistency requirements, a full redesign was not possible. Instead, I focused on incremental UX improvements that improved usability while preserving the existing visual identity.
        </p>

        <p><strong>Improving Visual Consistency</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Standardised spacing, typography, and reusable components</li>
          <li>Unified UI patterns across all sites</li>
          <li>Reduced cognitive load through consistency</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Enhancing Mobile Usability</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Introduced mobile-first layout improvements</li>
          <li>Improved spacing and prioritisation of key actions</li>
          <li>Reduced friction in browsing and interaction flows</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Simplifying Key Interactions</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Simplified user flows</li>
          <li>Improved CTA visibility and clarity</li>
          <li>Created more intuitive navigation patterns</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Improving Readability & Hierarchy</strong></p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Introduced clearer spacing and typography hierarchy</li>
          <li>Improved content grouping and layout structure</li>
          <li>Enhanced scanability and readability across devices</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="case-study-panel">
      <summary>Impact</summary>

      <div class="case-study-panel-content">
        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Improved performance across all platforms</li>
          <li>Created a more consistent UX across multiple brands</li>
          <li>Reduced development time through reusable components</li>
          <li>Established a scalable architecture for future growth</li>
          <li>Improved usability without requiring a full redesign</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="case-study-panel">
      <summary>Reflection</summary>

      <div class="case-study-panel-content">
        <p>This project strengthened my ability to:</p>

        <ul class="case-study-list">
          <li>Modernise legacy systems while maintaining live products</li>
          <li>Design scalable multi-brand architectures</li>
          <li>Deliver UX improvements within real-world constraints</li>
          <li>Balance technical decisions with user experience goals</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          It reinforced the importance of incremental improvement, showing that meaningful UX gains can be achieved without large-scale redesigns.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <div class="case-study-actions">
      <LinkButton url="/#projects" label="More Projects" />
    </div>

  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .case-study-hero {
    padding: 8rem 0 4rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-block-end: 3px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .case-study-hero .eyebrow {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .case-study-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .case-study-hero .intro {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .case-study-content {
    padding: 2rem 1rem ;
  }

  .case-study-panel {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
}

details.case-study-panel {
  border: 3px dashed;
  box-shadow: 6px 6px 0;
  background: var(--color-surface);
  overflow: hidden;
}

details.case-study-panel summary {
  list-style: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  color: var(--color-text);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  transition: background 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
}

details.case-study-panel summary::-webkit-details-marker {
  display: none;
}

details.case-study-panel summary::after {
  content: '▸';
  float: right;
  transition: transform 0.2s ease;
}

details.case-study-panel[open] summary::after {
  transform: rotate(90deg);
}

.case-study-panel-content {
  padding: 1.5rem;
}

.case-study-panel p,
.case-study-panel li {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  line-height: 1.9;
  font-size: 1rem;
}

.case-study-actions {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
}
</style>
